{ White is much better because White has space advantage in the center due to the e5-pawn, our pieces are much better coordinated, and there are many active plans, such as Rac1, attacking the Knight on c3 or Bc2 and Qd3, threatening Qh7. We shouldn't also forget about our main idea - Bxh6! Black, in turn, has the isolated pawn on d5 and the awfully coordinated Knights, which can never help in the defence of the King. One more possible plan is Qf2-Qg3 at the right moment followed by e6! }
