15. d6
{ Creating a far advanced protected passed pawn, which will be a headache for Black for ages. One possible idea could be a4, followed by Ra3. It has 3 purposes:   The first one is to double the Rooks on the b-file with Rb3 and Rfb1.  The second one is to shift the Rook to g3/h3 and suddenly an attack will pop out from nowhere!  The third one can be to fix the queenside with a5 which can help us in endgames. }
