{ It's often a good idea to place the Rook on the same file with the enemy Queen. }
14... Bd7
{ Developing the light-squared Bishop and liberating the c8-square for the Rook. }
15. cxd5 { Undoubling our pawns and making the d-pawn isolated. } 15... exd5
16. Qg3
{ Pinning the pawn on g7 and threatening Bh6. If Black neutralizes our plan on the kingside, we can occupy the b-file via Rb1. }
