{ If Black bravely accepts the sacrifice, they may quickly find themselves in a lost position. }
19. Qd2 { Defending the f4-Bishop and threatening Rhg1. } 19... Qh5
{ Black retreats the Queen in advance. } 20. Rhg1
{ We take control of the g-file and want to disturb the black Queen with Rg5 one more time. }
20... Nxc4
{ Black's attack on the queenside is absolutely hopeless unless we blunder a Queen in one move. }
21. Bxc4 dxc4 22. Rg5
{ The black Queen controls the vital g5-square, where the white Queen is going to land after the Rook sacrifice on g7. Therefore, we have to kick the Queen out of the h5-square. }
22... Qh4 23. Nf3
{ The black Queen still controls the g5-square, so we have to drive it away one more time. }
23... Qh3 { And we are ready now! } 24. Rxg7+
{ Boom! We expose the black King. } 24... Kxg7 25. Rg1+
{ Literally all the pieces are taking part in the attack now. } 25... Kh8 26.
Bh6
{ Since the black Queen hasn't controlled the g5-square, we totally crush our opponent! }
