{ Even the engine doesn't understand for a while what is wrong with this move. How are we, people, supposed to understand? }
17. Nf3 { Aiming to continue chasing the black Queen with Ng5. } 17... dxc4
{ The engine really likes this move for the first several minutes. } 18. Nh4
{ But then it spots this absolutely irrational move, that gives us a win. The Knight takes control of the f5-square and blocks the h-file as well. We're going to trap the Queen via Bf1 and pawn pushes. }
18... Nd5 { Attacking the f4-Bishop. } 19. Rd4
{ It seemed that the f4-Bishop was protected by the g3-pawn, but the pawn is overloaded, as it defends two pieces at the same time, the h4-Knight and the f4-Bishop. And again we want to attack the Queen with Bf1. }
19... Be7 { Black retreats the Bishop in order to attack the h4-Knight. } 20.
Bg5
{ A brilliant move! It turns out that the d4-Rook also x-rayed the g4 square, with the help of which the black Queen could have been rescued. We open up the fourth rank and control the g4-square with the Rook now. }
20... Bxg5 21. Bf1 { Finally, we trap the black Queen. } 21... Qxf1+
{ Black tries to get at least something for the Queen. } 22. Rxf1
{ Black has only two minor pieces and one pawn for a Queen, which isn't enough for full compensation. }
