15... Qxg5 16. Bxc5
{ It's important to keep the initiative especially when you have sacrificed some pieces. }
16... Rd8
{ Probably the most logical move. It's a natural desire to avoid the loss of the Rook. }
17. f4
{ Attacking the Queen and liberating the f3-square for the Rook in the future. }
17... Qf5
{ If Black moves the Queen to the h-file, then we can play Rf3, followed by Rh3, occupying the open h-file. }
18. Qe2
{ Of course, avoiding the exchange of the Queens and intending to push the pawn to g4. }
18... Kxh7 { The most principled reply. } 19. Be7
{ Exploiting the dark squares and aiming to set the Bishop on f6, where it will support our attack. }
19... Rd7 { Keeping the possibility to play ...Qd3 after g4. } 20. Bf6
{ Intending to give a mate via Rf3, Rh3 and Rh8. } *

