{ We will concentrate on the most popular and natural black move in this chapter. }
5. e4
{ It took me really a long time to choose the most practical and challenging move for White on the fifth move because there are many good continuations such as   5.a3  ,  5.Nf3  or  5.Bg5  I think, that we have to follow the fighting spirit of the classical variation of the Nimzo-Indian and go for the most principled lines. With 5. e4 we capture the center and force Black to show a decent level of opening knowledge or to think on their own from the first moves. }
