10... Bxc3+
{ It's too dry just to give up quite the strong dark-squared Bishop for free. }
11. bxc3
{ Black probably expected us to take with the Queen but we won't let ourselves be run by our opponent! It's essential to support the central pawn on d4 with another pawn. Don't worry that we have the doubled pawns along the c-file. They will be inevitably undoubled thanks to the c4-pawn. }
11... Nc6 12. O-O
{ As soon as your opponent doesn't have any threats and a quiet moment happens, it's time to follow one of the main principles of the opening - castle the King. }
