{ Besides these doubled pawns, the f6-square becomes a great aim for our Knight. }
14. a3 { The pin is quite annoying, so why not get rid of it? } 14... Bc5
{ Trading the Bishop on c3 would be a big concession.   14. ...Be7  is also possible but after  15.Ne4  The white Knight totally dominates the center and Black doesn't have a reasonable counterplay. }
15. Ne4
{ Centralizing the Knight and eyeing the f6-square. The c5-Bishop is attacked, indeed. }
15... Bd4 { Attacking the pawn on e5 which provides us a big space advantage. }
16. f4
{ The white doubled pawns on the f-file are healthy in contrast to the black doubled pawns on the h-file. The e5-pawn is protected well now and we are going to occupy the g-file with Rg1 as well as the f6-square with Nf6. }
