15. h3
{ An attempt to drive the g4-Knight away, followed by occupying the e5-square with the Knight. }
15... Nxf3
{ An important intermediate move, that forces us to show a decent level of calculation and accuracy. }
16. Bxh7+
{ Boom! There are two main principles of any attack: open up the opponent King and bring all the pieces into the attack. }
16... Kh8 { It's, by all means, the forced concession. } 17. hxg4
{ It seems quite tempting to sacrifice the Queen but to get the open h-file instead. }
17... Nxd2 18. Bg6+ { The only discovered check that wins back a Queen. } 18...
Kg8 19. Bxf7+
{ This is everything White can do in this position. It's unfortunately impossible to set a mating net. }
19... Rxf7 20. Rxd2 { Winning back a minor piece. } 20... Bxc3 21. bxc3
{ Black has damaged our pawn structure on the kingside and transposed to the opposite-colored Bishop ending, which has a big drawish tendency. }
