{ Black prepares to meet the attack with the already protected g7-pawn. } 16.
Kb1
{ Remember this prophylactic move! It's always worth considering to move the King to b1 after the queenside castling, as the King is much safer there and it defends all the pawns on the queenside. We are also going to defend the pinned c3-Knight in order to untie the d2-Queen, which would like to land on g5 to launch an attack. }
