8. Qb1 { It's a good idea to keep the Queen on the b1-h7 diagonal. } 8... Qxf6
9. Bd3
{ We create a battery along the b1-h7 diagonal, putting pressure on the h7-pawn. }
9... d5 10. Ne2
{ Before collecting the black pawns we need to develop the minor pieces. }
10... dxc4 11. Bxh7+
{ Taking on c4   11.Bxc4  would be inaccurate because of  11. ...b5!  and the position becomes unclear. }
11... Kh8 12. Bc2
{ We're going to castle kingside and develop the dark-squared Bishop to e3. Black has nothing for the sacrificed piece. }
