16... exd5
{ Otherwise, we could transfer the Knight to f4 and to h5 afterward. } 17. cxd5
{ Forcing Black to make an unpleasant decision. } 17... Nb8
{ If Black moves the Knight to e7   17. ...Ne7  then  18.d6  +-  Followed by Bc4.    After   17. ...Na5  we can make a fork with  18.b4  Winning back a minor piece. }
18. Rh5
{ Although we have only one pawn for the sacrificed Knight, our compensation is colossal. We're going to either push the d-pawn forward, followed by Bc4, or play Ng5, attacking the Rook and the pawns on h7 and f5. }
