{ Black has to liberate the d8-square for a Rook, otherwise, they just lose the pawn. }
17. Qd2
{ It's a good idea to transfer the major pieces to the semi-open d-file. }
17... Rfd8 18. Rd3
{ Counterintuitive though it is, we should retreat the Rook. After a natural move   18.O-O  Black can reply with  18. ...e5!  Now it's impossible to move the Rook back because of ...e4  19.e4  Nd4!  And the d6-Rook is trapped. }
18... d6 19. O-O
{ We intend to transfer one more major piece to the d-file in order to attack the d6-pawn. }
19... e5 { With the idea to make a fork. } 20. e4
{ Anyway, we're going to play Rd1 and put more pressure on the d6-pawn. } *

