{ Anyway, Black attempts to use the c-file in order to create the counterplay. }
17. cxd5
{ As our pawn is attacked, we are forced to take on d5, but why should we be upset? }
17... exd5 { It's by no means a good example of an isolated pawn. } 18. e4
{ The most effective strategy to exploit the opponent pinned piece is to attack it one more time. Black cannot save the d5-pawn, so we are much better. }
