{ We are getting the Queen out of the dangerous c-file and attacking the d7-pawn at the same time. }
13... Nxg3 14. hxg3
{ We are going either to grab space advantage with b4 or win the d7-pawn. }
14... Nb8
{ This move was played by the strong grandmaster Dmitrij Jakovenko. I can only imagine how hard and unpleasant this move was for him. }
15. g4
{ Since there have been no black pieces on the kingside, we should launch the attack there. We want to open up the h-file with g5 on the next move. }
15... Be7 { Black prevents g5. } 16. Nb5
{ Activating the Knight and attacking the a7-pawn. } 16... Ba6
{ X-raying the c4-pawn and intending to capture the b5-Knight. } 17. a4
{ We're getting ready to take back on b5 with the a-pawn. } *

