12... Rc8
{ Black is x-raying our Queen now.   12. ...Be7  13.Nb5  Nxg3  14.hxg3  transposes to  11. ... Be7     12. ...Nxg3  13.hxg3  Be7  transposes to  11. ... Be7 }
13. Qd3
{ We are getting the Queen out of the dangerous c-file and attacking the d7-pawn at the same time. }
13... Nxg3 14. hxg3
{ We are going either to grab space advantage with b4 or win the d7-pawn. }
14... Ba8 { The best move according to the engine. } 15. O-O
{ In my opinion, it's too dangerous to take the d7-pawn   15.Qxd7  because Black gets a dangerous counterplay after  15. ...Qf6  Black threatens to trap the Queen with Rfd8.  16.Qd2  Rfd8  17.Qc2  Rxd1  18.Qxd1?  Of course, it's much better to take with Knight, but even here Black gets quite an annoying counterplay on the queenside.  18. ...Bxa3!  Black is a pawn up. I think it's much safer just to castle kingside. }
15... Qf6 16. Rd2
{ We defend the b2-pawn so that the c3-Knight will be able to land on e4 with a fork. }
