{ This is the point of the pawn sacrifice. Black wants to win the exchange. }
17. Qd4 { The only reasonable retreat. The c8-Rook is still hanging. } 17...
Nb3
{ Taking on d1 immediately   17. ...Bxd1  doesn't bring much for Black.  18.Rxd1  We threaten to take on c8 and trap the Knight with b4.  18. ...Nb3  19.Qb4  Attacking the Knight.  19. ...Nc1  20.Bf1  The c1-Knight is running out of the moves and the c8-Rook is still hanging. It's impossible for Black to defend against all the threats. }
18. Nxc8 { All of a sudden, we sacrifice the Queen! } 18... Nxd4 19. Nxe7+
{ An important intermediate move. } 19... Qxe7 20. Rxd4
{ We want to win the exchange with Bd6. } 20... Nd5 { Blocking the d-file. }
21. bxa6
{ We have a Rook, a Bishop, and two pawns for a Queen, which must be more than enough. In addition, the outside passed a6-pawn creates a lot of problems for Black. }
