12... Bxc3+ 13. Qxc3
{ From now Black should always pay attention to the possible mate on g7. }
13... Ba6
{ Aiming to attack the c4-pawn with ...Rc8 on the next move.   13. ...d5  This is objectively the best continuation.  14.Be2  dxc4  15.g4  Instead of wasting a tempo on taking the c4-pawn, we should start the attack on the kingside immediately. We want to create the pawn storm with g5, h4, and so on. Black has to show a precise play to stop our attack. }
14. g4
{ A great way to use the pin along the c3-g7 diagonal. Taking on g4 would be a disaster because of mate in one with Qxg7. }
14... Rc8 { Black threatens to capture the c4-pawn, followed by ...d5. } 15. g5
{ Forcing Black to worsen the Knight. } 15... Ne8
{ The c4-pawn is still hanging. } 16. Qd4
{ Our Queen isn't x-rayed and ...Bxc4 isn't possible anymore. We're going to play Rd1, attacking the d7-pawn and push the h-pawn, launching the attack on the kingside. }
