{ The most logical and the strongest continuation! } 12... hxg5 13. hxg5
{ Forcing Black to take a terribly unpleasant decision about where to retreat the Knight. }
13... Ng8 { Retreating the Knight to h5 is equally bad. } 14. b4
{ Forcing Black to worsen one more piece. } 14... Bf8 15. Be2
{ Defending the f3-Knight, so that Black won't have any idea of a discovered attack with the c6-Knight. }
15... a6 16. Bb2
{ We have finished the development of the pieces and we are ready to castle queenside. In turn, the black pieces are awful. }
