{ A wonderful sacrifice that allows us to develop the dark-squared Bishop as fast as possible. }
12... Bxb4 13. Bb2
{ Don't worry that our c3-Knight is pinned, we're going to castle next move and this problem will disappear. }
13... Rg8 { Overprotecting the g7-pawn. } 14. O-O-O
{ The Knight wants to jump to d5 with the discovered attack. } 14... Qa5 15. e4
{ Trying to open up the center. } 15... f4 16. h4
{ We plan either to invade the fifth rank with Rg5 in order to worsen the position of the black Queen, or to push the e-pawn to open up the c2-h7 diagonal, attacking the h7-pawn. }
