4... c5
{ One of the main aims of an opening is to establish control of the center, which allows us to be flexible and move our pieces from one part of the board to another relatively easily. In addition, control of the center usually secures the advantage of space. So Black undermines our central d4-pawn. }
5. dxc5
{ If we support the d4-pawn with   5.e3  we might end up with an isolated pawn on d4 after  5. ...cxd4  6.exd4  d5!  And now it's Black who takes the initiative. So we have no choice but to capture the c5-pawn. However, I tend to estimate our chances to get the advantage in this variation to be pretty high. }
