{ Intending to play b4 on the next move. } 7... a6 { Black prevents Nb5. } 8.
b4
{ It's a key move in this position, as we win space on the queenside and worsen the position of the black Bishop. }
8... Be7 { Black threatens to win the c4-pawn. } 9. e4
