{ Black wants to develop the Bishop to b7. } 11. O-O Bb7 12. Bf4
{ It's a good idea to place the Bishop on f4 because it's attacking the weak d6-pawn. In addition, ...e5 isn't dangerous, as it weakens the d5-square a lot. }
12... Nbd7 13. Rac1 { We normally place our Rooks on c1 and d1. } 13... O-O 14.
Rfd1 { Putting more pressure on the d6-pawn. } 14... Rfd8 15. h3
{ A good prophylactic move. This is a standard Maroczy pawn structure, where our c- and e-pawns control the d5-square, fixing the weak d6-pawn. Black has less space and less flexible pieces. }
