14. exd4 { Otherwise, we lose the c3-Knight. } 14... Nxd4 15. Qd2
{ I find this move more logical than other retreats as we x-ray the d4-Knight, which will serve us well in the near future. }
15... Bxc5 { Black wins back a pawn and avoids annoying a3. } 16. Nge2
{ Attacking the d4-Knight. This is the point of retreating the Queen to d2 because we want to capture the d4-Knight, followed by Bb5, a discovered check. }
16... Kf8
{ Black wants to avoid the Bb5-check, but cannot castle kingside, because the h6-pawn is still hanging. }
17. Bc4 { Nevertheless, we should drive the active d4-Knight away. } 17... Be6
{ A small tactic. } 18. Bxe6
{ It would be a bad idea for us to capture the d4-Knight   18.Nxd4?  because of  18. ...Bxc4! }
18... Nxe6 19. Qd5
{ We're going to either win the b7-pawn or castle kingside or both. } *

