16. Kh1
{ The g1-a7 diagonal may become open one day, we should secure our King.   16.e4  would be a horrible blunder because of  16. ...dxe4  17.fxe4  Ng4!  And Black threatens ...Ne3, ...Bxh4 and ...Qxd4. }
16... b5
{ Black tries to create at least something on the queenside, even at the cost of weakening the c6-pawn. }
17. Bf5 { Pinning the e6-Knight. } 17... b4 18. Ne2
{ We're going to either put more pressure on the pinned e6-Knight with Nf4 or launch an attack in the center with e4. }
