{ It looks harmless, but there is poison in this move. } 12. Rc1
{ Activating a Rook.     12.Bd3?!  looks logical, but we just fall into a previously prepared trap.  12. ...Nc5!  A discovered attack!  13.Bxf5  Nxb3  14.axb3  We would be happy to play an intermediate move - Bxh7, but a pawn turns out to be on h6.  14. ...exf5  White is still better, but we have lost the lion's share of an advantage. }
12... Rd8 13. Be2
{ We could play this move one move earlier. The move order doesn't matter here. }
13... b6 14. O-O Bb7 15. Rfd1
{ We're going to hide a Bishop on e1, maintaining a Bishop pair advantage and increasing pressure on the c1-file. }
