9. Qc4 { We're attacking the c5-pawn and x-raying the c8-Bishop. } 9... Bxc3+
{ At least Black tested us whether we could find Qc4 or not. } 10. Qxc3
{ The c5-pawn is still hanging. } 10... Ne4
{ Black defends the c5-pawn with tempo but it's too careless to move one piece more than one time while other pieces have been still not developed. }
11. Qc2
{ The multitasking c2-Queen puts pressure on the e4-Knight as well as still x-rays the c8-Bishop. }
11... Nc6 { Black attacks the d4-pawn. } 12. e3
{ Defending the d4-pawn and intending to attack the pinned e4-Knight one more time with Bd3. }
12... cxd4
{ Objectively not the best move, but practically quite challenging, as it forces us to play precisely. }
13. Bd3
{ We attack the e4-Knight immediately, not wasting time on taking the d4-pawn. }
13... Qa5+ 14. b4
{ Not very difficult to find, but still the only move which gives an advantage. }
14... Nxb4 { Otherwise, Black just loses the e4-Knight. } 15. axb4
{ Sacrificing an exchange! } 15... Qxa1 16. O-O
{ Attacking the e4-Knight and thinking about a discovered attack along the back-rank. }
16... Nd6 17. exd4
{ It turns out that we have far more than enough compensation for an exchange. As the black Queen has run out of the moves, Black can hardly prevent Bf4 with a double attack. }
