{ For example, Black defends the c5-pawn immediately, leaving the Bishop on a5. }
10. b4
{ Gaining space on the queenside and getting rid of the pin on the a5-e1 diagonal. }
10... cxb4 { Otherwise, Black loses a pawn on c5. } 11. axb4
