{ 16.Nxd5  doesn't make any sense because after  16. ...exd5  the c4-Knight is protected. }
16... Nxc3 17. Bb2 { Developing a Bishop with tempo. } 17... Nd5
{ Attacking the b4-pawn. } 18. b5
{ We gain more space on the queenside and liberate the a3-f8 diagonal. Moreover, the b2-Bishop has an eye on the a3-square now. }
