8. Bxc3 { We get a Bishop pair advantage. } 8... cxd4
{ Black aims to get a symmetrical pawn structure as fast as possible. } 9. Nxd4
{ Taking on d4 with a Bishop   9.Bxd4  is worse as after  9. ...Nc6  10.Bc3  We are forced to retreat the Bishop back. }
9... e5
{ Black is kicking a Knight out of the center immediately, also gaining space.   9. ...Nc6  was played by the world champions Smyslov and Botvinnik ages ago.  10.O-O-O!  I can't say that we make our King much safer, but we, by all means, activate a Rook and defend the d4-Knight.  10. ...e5  11.Nxc6  Instead of going back we can take on c6 now.  11. ...Qxc6  12.Bxe5  Winning a pawn  12. ...Qxc2  13.Kxc2  Black doesn't have enough compensation for a pawn. }
