{ Developing a Bishop with tempo.   11. ...O-O  Black doesn't want to decide yet where to develop a Bishop.  12.Be2  Re8  13.O-O  Connecting the Rooks and intending to play Rfd1.  13. ...Qe4  14.Rfc1  Defending the c2-Queen.  14. ...Qxc2  15.Rxc2  Bf5  Anyway, Black develops a Bishop with tempo.  16.Rcc1  Ne4  Aiming to exchange a Bishop.  17.Be1  All we should do is to carefully keep a Bishop pair.  17. ...f6  18.Nd2  The e4-Knight is centralized and active, so why not trade it?  18. ...Nxd2  19.Bxd2  We enjoy our Bishop pair and intend to gain a space advantage on the queenside with b4. }
