11... a5 { Preventing b4. } 12. O-O
{ We have completed our development and we're waiting for Black's choice of a plan. }
12... Re8
{ This is a useful move, which Black needs anyway, as they overprotect the e5-pawn and improve a Rook. }
13. h3
{ Also a very helpful move - we create an escape hole and prevent ...Bg4. }
13... a4 { Fixing our pawns on the queenside. } 14. Rad1
{ When an opening has been already finished, we should seek the best squares for our pieces. The d1-one is surely the best for a Rook because we take control of an open file. }
14... Nd7 { Transferring a Knight either to c5 or to f8. } 15. Rd5
{ We have an eye on the e5-pawn, tying up the black d7-Knight to the defense of the e5-pawn. In addition, we want to double the Rooks on the d-file. }
15... f6 { Defending the e5-pawn one more time to make the d7-Knight free. }
16. Nh4
{ We proceed with finding the best squares for our pieces. In this case, we transfer a Knight to f5. }
16... Nb6
{ Attacking our Rook and opening up the c8-Bishop.   16. ...Nf8?!  Too passive.  17.Nf5  Completing our original plan.  17. ...Qf7  Black threatens to capture the f5-Knight, followed by ...Ne7 with a fork.  18.Rb5!  Quite an unexpected decision! We have an eye on the b7-pawn, preventing Black from developing a Bishop. }
17. Rb5
{ Although the b-file has been closed, it's still a good idea to transfer a Rook to b5 as it puts pressure on the queenside and prevents Black from activating the Queen to c5. }
17... Be6 { Developing a Bishop with tempo. } 18. Nf5
{ Completing our plan to improve a Knight. } 18... Qd7 19. Nd6
{ What a move! Unbelievable! We simply move our Knight to a blank square, which is controlled by two black pieces. }
19... Qxd6
{ 19. ...cxd6  20.Rxb6  Black gets one more problem - a weakness on d6. We're going to play Rd1 to exploit it. }
20. c5 { That's the point of luring the black Queen to d6 - to give a fork. }
20... Qd8 21. cxb6 cxb6 22. Qe4
{ Technically Black is a pawn up, but the b6-pawn will most likely fall, leaving us with a Bishop pair advantage and more active pieces. }
