13. h3 { As you can see, we play this move in all variations. } 13... Nd7
{ Transferring a Knight to c5.   13. ...Re8  transposes to the previous line. }
14. Bd3 { We're moving a Bishop to e4 with tempo. } 14... g6 15. Be4
{ The Bishop is much more active on e4 as it has an eye on the c6-Knight and is ready to go to d5 at some point. }
15... Nd8
{ Avoiding doubling the pawns after Bxc6 and intending to finally activate a Knight with ...Nc5. }
16. Bb4 { Provoking Black to make an unpleasant decision. } 16... c5
{ 16. ...Nc5  would be even worse because Black voluntarily sets up a pin for themselves.  17.Ne1  with the idea to attack the c5-Knight with Nd3. }
17. Bc3 { Eyeing the e5-pawn. } 17... Nf6 18. Bd5
{ The e5-pawn is still hanging and we are ready to take back on d5, creating a central passed pawn. }
*

