14. d5 { We should turn on our main trump - a Bishop pair. } 14... Rg6
{ In my opinion, the g-file promises Black fewer prospects than the h-file. }
15. Nd4 { Attacking the e6- and f5-pawns. } 15... Qg5
{ As the white Knight has left the kingside, it makes sense for Black to create some threats there.   15. ...Nf8  was played in the rapid game Carlsen - Hou  16.Bd3  Attacking the e4-Knight  16. ...Qg5  17.f4  Instead of playing g3 we can afford to push the f-pawn immediately.  17. ...Qh5  18.Bxe4  fxe4  19.Rf2  Accurately defending the g2-pawn and planning to break the position with f5.     15. ...exd5  doesn't make sense at all.  16.Nxf5  Qe6  17.Ng3!  An important move that protects the kingside very well. }
