{ 16. ...Nf8  is also worth considering  17.f4  Driving away the black Queen.  17. ...Qh4  18.Bf3!  Intending to take the e4-Knight.  18. ...Nxg3  is a desperate attempt to create an attack.  19.hxg3  Qxg3  20.Bg2  Qxe3  21.Rf2  Black has nothing for a sacrificed piece. }
17. cxd5 { As the c-file has become open, we want to win the c7-pawn. } 17...
Bxd5 18. Rad1
{ There is no reasonable way to prevent Qxc7, Nf3 and Nxf5 at the same time. }
