15. h4 { Physically stopping ...h4. } 15... Nd7
{ Transferring a Knight to c5. } 16. Be2
{ The black pawns are poisoned.   16.Nxh5?  Nc5!  Attacking the b3- and e4-pawns at the same time.  17.Qc2  b5!  The white queenside is falling apart.     16.Qxd6  is not that bad but after  16. ...Nc5  Black develops a huge initiative.  17.Qxd8  Rfxd8  Black has full compensation for a pawn thanks to the active Knights and a great outpost on d4. }
16... Nc5 17. Rb1
{ Defending the b3-pawn and intending to push it forward. The weak d6-pawn makes Black play precisely and creatively, which is by no means easy. }
