5... b6 { Black wants to transpose to the Queen's Indian. } 6. Bg5
{ Pinning the f6-Knight. } 6... h6 { An attempt to get rid of the g5-d8 pin. }
7. Bh4 { Still maintaining a pin. } 7... g5 8. Bg3 Ne4
{ The Knight is finally free! } 9. Qc2
{ Attacking the e4-Knight. We're not going to tolerate the e4-Knight for a long time. }
9... Bb7 10. e3 d6 11. f3 { Driving away the e4-Knight. } 11... Nxg3 12. hxg3
{ On one hand, Black deprives us of a Bishop pair advantage, on the other hand, the h-file becomes open and our h1-Rook has been brought into the game without playing a single move. }
12... Nd7 13. g4 { Fixing the black pawns on the kingside. } 13... Qe7 14. Ne2
{ With the idea to develop a Knight to g3. } 14... O-O-O 15. Ng3
{ Intending to castle queenside and taking control over the center with e4. } *

