{ Mamedyarov wins back a pawn and threatens Be7 with a double attack. } 20...
Nc4 21. Nb5
{ 21.Rb1  is a little bit better as we prevent Black from developing the light-squared Bishop. }
21... Rf7
{ This is a totally understandable decision but it was better to sacrifice a pawn with  21. ...Bd7  22.Nc7  Rac8  23.Nxd5  Kg7!  Black has almost enough compensation for a pawn because the white pieces are not coordinated well enough and the c3-pawn is quite weak. }
22. Bf4 { Preparing Nc7 again. } 22... Bh3 23. Rd1
