1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. e4 d6 6. e5 dxe5 7. dxe5 Ng4 8. Nf3
Nc6 9. Bf4 f6 10. Bd3 fxe5
{ We have analyzed only  10....Ngxe5  in this chapter  and  10....h6  in this chapter.  This is clearly a mistake as it allows White to smoothly win the h7-pawn. }
11. Bg5 { Moving the Bishop with tempo. } 11... Be7 12. Bxh7+
{ Winning back a pawn and leaving Black with an awful pawn structure. } 12...
Kh8 13. Bxe7 Qxe7
{ Black wants to centralize a Knight with ...Nd4, attacking the f3-Knight and opening up the f-file. }
14. Be4 { White should defend the f3-Knight in advance. } 14... Nd4 15. Qd3
{ It looks weird to place the Queen on d3, but Navara intends to sacrifice a Knight on e5 to transfer the Queen to h3. }
15... Qf6 { Polak prevents Nxe5 and tries to put more pressure on the f-file. }
16. h3 { Why not drive away the active black Knight? } 16... Nh6 17. O-O
{ White has fully completed development, meanwhile, the black Bishop is still on c8. }
17... Bd7 18. Nb5
{ An excellent move! We always should think about the pieces on the board, how good they are and which pieces we would like to trade. The d4-Knight is the only active black minor piece. Navara understands it very well and suggests Black exchanging the Knights. }
18... c5
{ An attempt to save the Knight on d4   18. ...Bxb5  would lead to opening up the c-file.  19.cxb5  The b5-pawn fixes the black pawns on the queenside. }
19. Nbxd4 { First completing the original plan. } 19... exd4 20. Bxb7
{ Winning a pawn for free. } 20... Rab8 21. Be4 Nf5
{ 21. ...Rxb2  It turns out that Black cannot take the b2-pawn because of  22.Qa3!  Attacking everything: the b2-Rook, the a7-pawn, and the c5-pawn. The black position is falling apart. }
22. Rae1 { Navara is taking control over the semi-open e-file. } 22... Nd6 23.
b3
{ Navara buries once and for all the hope of Polak to grab either the b2- or c4-pawns. }
23... e5 24. Bg6 { Attacking the e5-pawn. } 24... Bxh3 25. Nxe5
{ White wants to give mate in three with Qxh3. } 25... Bf5 26. Bxf5 Nxf5 27.
Nd7 { The Knight lands on d7 with a lovely fork. Black resigned. } *

