1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 Bb4 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 g5 8. Bg3
Ne4 9. Qc2 c5 10. dxc5
{ We have finally a transposition to our 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 exd5 chapter. }
10... Qa5 11. Rc1 Qxa2 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. Bxd7+ Nxd7 14. Ne2 Qc4
{ It was much better first to take the c3-Knight.   14. ...Nxc3  15.Nxc3  and only then  15. ...Qc4  because White cannot castle short immediately. }
15. O-O { There is no obstacle to castle short, fortunately. } 15... Bxc3
{ One more mistake by Nguyen, Thai Dai Van. It's hard to understand the reason why he voluntarily gave up his dark-squared Bishop.   15. ...Ndxc5  was much better. }
16. Nxc3
{ There is nothing wrong with this move but it was even better to play  16.Qd1!  The idea behind this move is to take back on c3 with the c1-Rook. For example,  16. ...Ndxc5  17.Nxc3  Nxc3  18.Rxc3  The d5-pawn falls. }
16... Ndxc5
{ After  16. ...Nxc3  17.Qxc3  Qxc3  18.Rxc3  The black position is awful but not completely lost yet. }
17. Qd1
{ Getting the Queen out of the c-file to include the c1-Rook into the game. }
17... Nd3
{ The black Knights look active but they are in fact extremely vulnerable. }
18. Nxe4 Qxe4 19. Rc3
{ It turns out that Black is forced to give up the material. } 19... Ne5
{ If  19. ...Nb4  then  20.f3  Qe7  Black has to keep the b4-Knight protected.  21.Qd4  Attacking the h8-Rook and the b4-Knight.  21. ...O-O  22.Rc7!  Black loses the b4-Knight.     After  19. ...Nxb2  there is a very enjoyable move  20.Qa1!  X-raying the h8-Rook.  20. ...Nc4  21.Rxc4!  A discovered attack! }
20. f3 { Black is forced to leave the d5-pawn. } 20... Qf5 21. Qxd5
{ It's hard to believe that Black can ever survive with such a bad King. }
21... f6 22. Rc7 { A Rook on the seventh rank is a beast. } 22... Rd8 23. Qb5+
Kf8 24. Qb4+ { With the idea to invade the seventh rank with the Queen. } 24...
Kg8 25. Qe7
{ Threatening mate in one with Qg7 and attacking the d8-Rook. Black resigned. This game shows how difficult it is to play this variation for Black. They have to demonstrate precise knowledge of the opening, otherwise, they can end up in a position like this very quickly. }
